The Impact of Coronavirus On Arts Organizations

Rena Cohen

11/12/2020

This summer, I had the opportunity to intern with Americans for the Arts (AFTA), a national arts advocacy organization. In March, AFTA released a survey about the impact of coronavirus on the arts that has since been filled out by over 18,000 individual arts organizations. For my final project in GOV 50, I hope to build models to estimate the economic impact on these organizations based on a variety of explanatory variables. By predicting impact in this way, we can better understand how to build policies that will effectively help these organizations. Here are some initial data visualizations relating to this project.
